    "However, the principle is also recognised in other legal systems, like the US, sometimes under the formula \"as low as reasonably achievable\" (ALARA) ALARP-type approaches involve a proportionality review of risk reduction measures so that they are not exorbitant to the improvement gained (Bai & Jin, 2016)."
